\par\plain { For a few moments, Moto\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s pod descended alongside the burning wreck, putting him near enough to witness the awesome power of The Experiment\u8217\'92s final, frenzied moments.}
\par\plain {There he saw how the ship\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s command capsule had been hollowed out by the wind and flames, and how it\u8217\'92s metal plating emitted a great white light, gradienting to a soft red near the midsection, and how behind it all a thick, rich, black plume trailed for hundreds of meters as some synthetic material began to burn. Whatever exterior elements still clung to the hurtling wreck soon began to peel backwards, roots melting, before breaking off to join the rest of the debris and fertilize the planet\u8217\'92s atmosphere.}
\par\plain {Moto watched in horror as the compressive strength of the ship\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s central skeleton failed.The whole thing crumpled, then exploded in a deafening blast. He knew his pod was near enough to be hit by its concussive shock. When it came, it threw his pod into an end-over-end tumble, and through the frenzy he was able to catch glimpses of a monstrous, white, ice crystal plume, the head of a massive anvil thunderstorm, rushing up to devour him.}
